[src:mechanism-design/mechanism-design] It considers the set of intervals $\left[{\underline {\theta }},{\overline {\theta }}\right]$ in the nonmonotonic region of $x(\theta )$ over which it might flatten the schedule.
[src:mechanism-design/mechanism-design] Condition two ensures that the $x(\theta )$ satisfying the optimal control problem reconnects to the schedule in the original problem at the interval boundaries (no jumps).
[src:mechanism-design/mechanism-design] Any $x(\theta )$ satisfying the necessary conditions must be flat because it must be monotonic and yet reconnect at the boundaries.
